sentences: Sean McAloon (1923–1998) was a piper and pipe maker from Northern Ireland.
He emigrated to the United States in 1964, but after a year he returned to Ireland.
He emigrated to the United States in 1964, but after a year he returned to Ireland.
He spent eight months working as a builder's labourer in Dublin, but moved to Belfast in 1966 to be closer to his family.
